title: Bold and ‘brat’: Marks & Spencer bets on womenswear to revive autumn fortunes
summary: A retailer is working to recover from a summer cyber-attack by offering a new selection of fashion items targeted at a broader age demographic. title: If Labour admitted there is a genocide in Gaza, it would have to admit its own hand in it | Owen Jones

title: Labour must rethink growth strategy to curb rise of far right, says top economist
summary: Former Bank of England chief economist Andy Haldane emphasizes the urgent need for investment in neglected communities to combat rising populist sentiments. He argues that addressing economic disparities is crucial for fostering social cohesion. Haldane's comments highlight the growing concerns over the impact of neglect on community well-being.
